# Local development overrides for `dotnet run --project Nag.Api`.
#
# Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) and edit. dotenv.net loads both
# `.env` and `.env.local` in Debug builds (see Program.cs); .NET
# config uses `__` (double underscore) to separate JSON sections,
# e.g. `Nag__DeviceToken__Secret` → `Nag:DeviceToken:Secret`.

# HMAC-SHA256 signing key for per-device bearer tokens. Generate with:
#   openssl rand -base64 48
# Rotating invalidates every previously-issued device token, so on the
# next request mobile clients hit 401 and re-register.
Nag__DeviceToken__Secret=dev-only-replace-me-with-`openssl rand -base64 48`"

# Optional. DEBUG-only. Account/device GUID baked into tokens minted by
# `GET /dev/token` (used by the Swagger UI auto-authorize script *and*
# by the Expo app when `EXPO_PUBLIC_NAG_DEV_AUTH=1`, so swagger and the
# app share a tenant out of the box). Defaults to 1111…/2222… if unset;
# override here to match a real account in your local Postgres so
# commands resolve against existing aggregates.
# Nag__DeviceToken__DevAccountId=
# Nag__DeviceToken__DevDeviceId=

# Optional. Clerk Frontend API URL for JWT verification. Leave unset to
# disable Clerk-mode entirely (the auth handler will 401 any JWT-shaped
# bearer). Mobile-only deployments don't need this.
# Nag__ClerkIssuer=https://your-instance.clerk.accounts.dev

# Optional. Postgres connection string override; otherwise the value in
# appsettings.json is used (assumes `docker compose up -d` from this dir).
# ConnectionStrings__Nag=Host=localhost;Port=5432;Database=nag;Username=postgres;Password=postgres

# Optional. Point the local backend at a Neon database — useful for
# smoke-testing the LambdaSecrets TLS path (sslmode + verify-full)
# against the real cloud endpoint before deploying. When set, this
# wins over `ConnectionStrings__Nag` and `appsettings.json` because
# `LambdaSecrets.HydrateFromEnvironment` rewrites the connection
# string into the in-memory config provider. Pull the URI from Pulumi
# with `pulumi stack output --show-secrets --cwd infra connectionUri`.
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://USER:PASS@HOST.neon.tech/nag?sslmode=verify-full
